==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cathode
<hw>Cath"ode</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ descent; <?/
down + <?/ way.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The part of a voltaic
battery by which the electric current leaves substances through which it
passes, or the surface at which the electric current passes out of the
electrolyte; the negative pole; -- opposed to <xex>anode</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Faraday.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cathode ray</b></col> <fld>(Phys.)</fld>, <cd>a kind of
ray generated at the cathode in a vacuum tube, by the electrical
discharge<-- X-ray -->.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cathodic</ent>⟦br⟧
